############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION a. [`f(A) = \{3,4,5,6,7,8,9,10,11\}\text{.}`]
a. [`\newcommand{\inv}{^{-1}}f\inv(\{1,2\}) = \{001, 010, 100, 011, 101, 110, 002, 020, 200\}\text{.}`]
a. [`\newcommand{\inv}{^{-1}}f\inv(3) = \{003, 030, 300, 012, 021, 102, 201, 120, 210, 111\}`] a. [`\newcommand{\inv}{^{-1}}f\inv(28) = \emptyset`] (since the largest sum of three digits is [`9+9+9 = 27`]) a. Part (c) proves that [`f`] is not injective. The output 3 is assigned to 10 different inputs.
a. Part (d) proves that [`f`] is not surjective. There is an element of the codomain (28) which is not assigned to any inputs.
END_PGML_SOLUTION
############################################################ # End Problem ############################################################
ENDDOCUMENT();

