############################################################ # Header ############################################################ COMMENT('Authored in PreTeXt'); TEXT(beginproblem());
############################################################ # PG Setup ############################################################ Context("IntegerFunctions"); $ans1 = Compute(2^9); $ans2 = Compute(C(9,5)); $ans1 = Compute(2^4); $ans4 = Compute("C(9,0)+C(9,2)+C(9,4)+C(9,6)+C(9,8)");
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML Let [`A = \{1,2,3,\ldots,9\}\text{.}`] a. How many subsets of [`A`] are there? That is, find [`\newcommand{\pow}{\mathcal P}|\pow(A)|\text{.}`] Explain.
[_____]{$ans1}
a. How many subsets of [`A`] contain exactly 5 elements? Explain.
[_____]{$ans2}
a. How many subsets of [`A`] contain only even numbers? Explain.
[_____]{$ans3}
a. How many subsets of [`A`] contain an even number of elements? Explain.
[_____]{$ans4}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION a. There are [`512`] subsets. This is [`2^9\text{,}`] which makes sense because we are deciding yes or no on whether to include each element of [`A`] in the subset.
a. Of the nine elements in [`A\text{,}`] we must choose five of them to be in the subset. So [`{9 \choose 5} = 126\text{.}`]
a. For each of the 9 elements from [`A\text{,}`] we must decide yes or no on whether to include them in the subset. However, for the odd numbers, we only have one choice: no. So there are only 4 elements we have two choices for, so the answer is [`2^4 = 16\text{.}`] (Note, if you wish to exclude the empty set - it does not contain odd numbers, but no evens either - then you could subtract 1).
a. Count the number of subsets with each possible even cardinality:
[``` {9 \choose 0} + {9 \choose 2} + {9\choose 4} + {9 \choose 6} + {9 \choose 8} = 256 ```]
END_PGML_SOLUTION
############################################################ # End Problem ############################################################
ENDDOCUMENT();

####################################### ### Generated from PreTeXt source ### on 2018-07-27T14:33:58-06:00 ### ### http://mathbook.pugetsound.edu ### ####################################### ## DBsubject() ## DBchapter() ## DBsection() ## Level() ## KEYWORDS() ## TitleText1(Discrete Mathematics) ## EditionText1() ## AuthorText1(Oscar Levin) ## Section1(not reported) ## Problem1(2.2.4) ## Author() ## Institution() ## Language(en-US)
