############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML How many shortest lattice paths start at (3,3) and a. end at (10,10)?
[_____]{$ans1}
a. end at (10,10) and pass through (5,7)?
[_______]{$ans2}
a. end at (10,10) and avoid (5,7)?
[_______]{$ans3}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION a. [`{14 \choose 7} = 3432`] paths. The paths all have length 14 (7 steps up and 7 steps right), we just select which 7 of those 14 should be up. a. [`{6 \choose 2}{8\choose 5} = 840`] paths. First travel to (5,7), and then continue on to (10,10). a. [`{14 \choose 7} - {6\choose 2}{8 \choose 5}`] paths. Remove all the paths that you found in part (b).
END_PGML_SOLUTION
