############################################################ # PG Setup ############################################################ Context("IntegerFunctions"); $ans1 = Compute("C(20,4)"); $ans2 = Compute("P(20,4)"); $ans3 = Compute("C(23,4)"); $ans4 = Compute("20^4");
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML _Conic_, your favorite math themed fast food drive-in offers 20 flavors which can be added to your soda. You have enough money to buy a large soda with 4 added flavors. How many different soda concoctions can you order if: a. You refuse to use any of the flavors more than once?
[_____]{$ans1}
a. You refuse repeats but care about the order the flavors are added?
[_____]{$ans2}
a. You allow yourself multiple shots of the same flavor?
[_____]{$ans3}
a. You allow yourself multiple shots, and care about the order the flavors are added?
[_____]{$ans4}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION a. [`{20 \choose 4}`] sodas (order does not matter and repeats are not allowed).
a. [`P(20, 4) = 20\cdot 19\cdot 18 \cdot 17`] sodas (order matters and repeats are not allowed).
a. [`{23 \choose 4}`] sodas (order does not matter and repeats are allowed; 4 stars and 19 bars).
a. [`20^4`] sodas (order matters and repeats are allowed; 20 choices 4 times).
END_PGML_SOLUTION
############################################################ # End Problem ############################################################
